1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,940
The next day in a written test, she included this question.

2
00:00:05,230 --> 00:00:10,030
My full name has six letters. The first one is M. I pick up things. What am I?

3
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:19,690
Fifty percent of the students wrote mother. Amen, huh?

4
00:00:21,940 --> 00:00:23,040
Another take on that.

5
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:30,560
Dr. G. Campbell Morgan was a great preacher, and he had four sons, and they were all great preachers.

6
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:35,860
And someone once came into the drawing room and asked, when the family was all there,

7
00:00:35,860 --> 00:00:41,760
They said to one of the sons, which one is the greatest preacher in your family?

8
00:00:43,260 --> 00:00:44,440
That's a tough question.

9
00:00:45,550 --> 00:00:50,910
And he had great admiration for his father, and he looked at his father, and he said without a moment's hesitation,

10
00:00:51,550 --> 00:00:55,270
Mother, because she lived it.

11
00:00:56,070 --> 00:00:56,830
She lived it.

12
00:00:56,910 --> 00:01:00,570
Therefore, she's the greatest preacher in that family.

13
00:01:01,680 --> 00:01:08,770
Hey, friends, mothers, we know this, are a powerful force on planet Earth as designed by God.

14
00:01:09,570 --> 00:01:13,350
And so on this Mother's Day, as part of this church, on behalf of the church,

15
00:01:13,830 --> 00:01:20,110
our hats off are to you, all mothers, grandmothers, great-grandmothers, aspiring mothers, you name it.

16
00:01:20,110 --> 00:01:24,370
We bless you and we thank you for your ministry and your hard work.

17
00:01:26,320 --> 00:01:27,920
Is there an amen out there? Amen.

18
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:32,420
Now, before I continue, I wanted to highlight somebody.

19
00:01:32,460 --> 00:01:33,440
I did this last year.

20
00:01:35,390 --> 00:01:38,650
And I want just, as we talk about a biblical character this morning,

21
00:01:38,710 --> 00:01:43,670
I want to share somebody who lives out these values today,

22
00:01:43,810 --> 00:01:45,270
who's actually here in our midst.

23
00:01:46,490 --> 00:01:48,510
This individual is a special woman.

24
00:01:48,510 --> 00:01:59,690
She is a mother, a grandmother, trained as a chemist, a musician, a missionary,

25
00:01:59,690 --> 00:02:08,290
a teacher even today. She's a godly woman and a leader, and she's sitting at the organ right

26
00:02:08,290 --> 00:02:30,690
behind me. You want to say something? We appreciate you. Surprise. You want to say anything?

27
00:02:40,850 --> 00:02:47,450
Betty Lyon lives out many of the themes in the book of Deborah, or rather in the book of Judges

28
00:02:47,450 --> 00:02:52,630
from the character of Deborah. We want to honor you this morning as a leader, as a godly woman,

29
00:02:52,630 --> 00:02:55,010
in a variety of ways, you have been a real

30
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:56,710
leader for us.

31
00:02:56,970 --> 00:02:58,710
We thank you. You want to say anything?

32
00:02:58,990 --> 00:03:00,630
I don't know what to say.

33
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:04,300
This is such a surprise.

34
00:03:07,950 --> 00:03:08,970
I just praise the Lord

35
00:03:08,970 --> 00:03:10,890
for each one of you and thank

36
00:03:10,890 --> 00:03:12,870
the Lord for you and

37
00:03:12,870 --> 00:03:14,670
pray that we all might follow

38
00:03:14,670 --> 00:03:16,310
the Lord as long as we live.

39
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,520
Thank you so much.

40
00:03:18,700 --> 00:03:20,980
Thank you for your ministry. I appreciate you.

41
00:03:20,980 --> 00:03:25,160
You're welcome.

42
00:03:30,010 --> 00:03:31,590
She had no idea we were doing that.

43
00:03:31,590 --> 00:03:36,880
And I don't usually pick on people from the pulpit, but this is special day.

44
00:03:38,890 --> 00:03:45,170
Well, as is customary on Mother's Day, I like to highlight various women in Scripture

45
00:03:45,170 --> 00:03:50,970
that make a big impact on the kingdom of God and that bless us across the centuries.

46
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:53,900
And so this morning is going to be no different.

47
00:03:54,020 --> 00:03:56,700
And today I want to look at a woman from the Old Testament.

48
00:03:57,320 --> 00:04:01,780
We're going to look at Deborah and see some of the principles of leadership

49
00:04:01,780 --> 00:04:04,520
that come out of this great woman in the Old Testament.

50
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:09,720
And so as parents, as grandparents, as employers, employees, and so on,

51
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:13,440
we all have leadership roles in the world today.

52
00:04:14,570 --> 00:04:18,450
And so we can learn from this great and mighty and godly woman

53
00:04:18,450 --> 00:04:20,710
as she is an encouragement to all of us.

54
00:04:21,050 --> 00:04:23,630
And so this morning we're going to turn to the book of Judges.

55
00:04:24,170 --> 00:04:26,970
And I want to give you a quick backdrop on this text.

56
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:30,390
The book of Judges covers 300 years of history.

57
00:04:31,310 --> 00:04:36,510
And during this time, God's people are now living in the promised land,

58
00:04:36,630 --> 00:04:37,630
but they have no king.

59
00:04:38,330 --> 00:04:39,550
There's no one leader.

60
00:04:40,290 --> 00:04:43,450
It's a time between Joshua and the first king.

61
00:04:44,530 --> 00:04:48,330
And in essence, there's nobody calling the shots.

62
00:04:49,380 --> 00:04:52,040
There's nobody bringing stability to the land.

63
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:54,880
And so there was a time when, as the Bible says,

64
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:58,700
the people did what was right in their own eyes.

65
00:04:58,700 --> 00:05:04,470
and they found themselves in a cycle that went over and over.

66
00:05:04,570 --> 00:05:05,490
It looked like this.

67
00:05:06,190 --> 00:05:08,530
The people would be doing well, stage one.

68
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:13,110
And then after years of prosperity, they'd turn their backs on God.

69
00:05:13,210 --> 00:05:14,210
That was stage two.

70
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:18,230
Stage three, God would send an enemy to oppress them.

71
00:05:19,190 --> 00:05:21,770
Stage four, the people would cry out to God.

72
00:05:22,490 --> 00:05:27,130
Stage five, God sends a deliverer and the people start doing well again.

73
00:05:27,130 --> 00:05:31,190
And that cycle repeats over and over and over.

74
00:05:33,050 --> 00:05:39,790
And this story this morning from Judges chapter 4 takes place during one of those cycles.

75
00:05:41,310 --> 00:05:42,030
And so we begin.

76
00:05:43,670 --> 00:05:50,300
After Ehud's death, the Israelites again did what was evil in the sight of the Lord.

77
00:05:51,410 --> 00:05:56,030
So the Lord handed them over to King Jabin of Hazor, a Canaanite king.

78
00:05:56,030 --> 00:06:01,770
And the commander of his army was Sisera, who lived in Herosheth Hagoyim.

79
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:10,860
Sisera, who had 900 iron chariots, ruthlessly oppressed the Israelites for 20 years.

80
00:06:12,910 --> 00:06:16,350
Then the Israelites cried out to the Lord for help.

81
00:06:17,950 --> 00:06:23,490
Deborah, the wife of Lapidoth, was a prophet who had become a judge in Israel.

82
00:06:23,490 --> 00:06:30,830
She would hold court under the palm of Deborah, which stood between Ramah and Bethel in the hill country of Ephraim.

83
00:06:31,430 --> 00:06:35,110
And the Israelites came to see her to settle their disputes.

84
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:42,300
One day, she sent for Barak, son of Abinoam, who lived in Kadesh in the land of Naphtali.

85
00:06:42,580 --> 00:06:47,100
And she said to him, this is what the Lord, the God of Israel, commands you.

86
00:06:47,860 --> 00:06:53,260
Assemble 10,000 warriors from the tribes of Naphtali and Zebulun at Mount Tabor.

87
00:06:53,260 --> 00:06:56,960
and I will lure Sisera, commander of Jabin's army,

88
00:06:57,420 --> 00:07:00,440
along with his chariots and warriors to the Kishon River,

89
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:03,680
and there I will give you victory over him.

90
00:07:04,990 --> 00:07:09,750
Barak told her, I will go, but only if you go with me.

91
00:07:10,850 --> 00:07:12,130
Very well, she replied.

92
00:07:12,810 --> 00:07:16,630
I will go with you, but since you have made this choice,

93
00:07:17,330 --> 00:07:18,870
you will receive no honor,

94
00:07:19,620 --> 00:07:23,320
for the Lord's victory over Sisera will be at the hands of a woman.

95
00:07:24,340 --> 00:07:26,640
So Deborah went with Barak to Kadesh.

96
00:07:26,820 --> 00:07:30,360
At Kadesh, Barak called together the tribes of Zebulun and Naphtali,

97
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:33,200
and 10,000 warriors marched up with them.

98
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:36,580
Deborah also marched with them.

99
00:07:37,790 --> 00:07:38,690
Can you imagine that?

100
00:07:40,540 --> 00:07:43,760
Now Haber the Kenite, a descendant of Moses' brother-in-law, Hobab,

101
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,380
had moved away from the other members of the tribe

102
00:07:46,380 --> 00:07:50,000
and pitched his tent by the oak of Zanaim near Kadesh.

103
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:54,420
When Sisera was told that Barak's son of Abinoam had gone up to Mount Tabor,

104
00:07:54,420 --> 00:07:59,180
he called for all 900 of his iron chariots and all of his warriors,

105
00:07:59,580 --> 00:08:02,720
and they marched from Hereshoth Hagayim to the Gishon River.

106
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:05,200
And then Deborah said to Barak,

107
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:06,240
Get ready.

108
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:09,840
Today the Lord will give you victory over Sisera,

109
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:12,960
for the Lord is marching ahead of you.

110
00:08:13,620 --> 00:08:18,160
And so Barak led his 10,000 warriors down the slopes of Mount Tabor into battle.

111
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:24,520
When Barak attacked the Lord through Sisera and all his charioteers and warriors into a panic,

112
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:29,060
And then Sisera leaped down from his chariot and escaped on foot.

113
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:33,420
Barak chased the enemy and their chariots all the way to Herosheth Hagoyim,

114
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:38,280
killing all of Sisera's warrior, and not a single one was left.

115
00:08:38,920 --> 00:08:40,060
We're going to stop right there.

116
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:49,810
The Israelites had done evil in the sight of the Lord and slaved for 20 years.

117
00:08:50,230 --> 00:08:53,510
And after intense oppression, they call out to the Lord,

118
00:08:53,510 --> 00:08:57,250
And God brings this woman, Deborah, onto the scene.

119
00:08:58,700 --> 00:09:03,740
Now Deborah was a woman who was appointed and chosen by God to be a prophet.

120
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:09,620
And a prophet in those days was one who spoke directly for God.

121
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:11,760
Here's how it worked.

122
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:16,920
If a prophet spoke untruth in the name of God, they were to be killed.

123
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:20,180
This is serious business.

124
00:09:20,180 --> 00:09:26,410
and Deborah carried that mantle of being a prophet of God.

125
00:09:28,780 --> 00:09:32,000
Well, Deborah, the prophet, through her skills and her prophetic voice,

126
00:09:32,140 --> 00:09:33,980
became a judge in the land.

127
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:40,300
And later in chapter 5, verse 7, it even says she arose as a mother in Israel.

128
00:09:41,670 --> 00:09:44,930
So on this Mother's Day, I want to dote for a moment on Deborah.

129
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:51,060
First of all, the text says that people came to her to settle disputes.

130
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:54,980
She was a leader by her, number one, by her wisdom.

131
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,140
She was a leader by her wisdom.

132
00:09:58,620 --> 00:10:01,180
Wisdom is applied knowledge.

133
00:10:02,340 --> 00:10:05,760
One dimension of wisdom is the ability to see the big picture

134
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:07,680
and to know what to do.

135
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:09,780
That was her role.

136
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:13,680
Settle disputes, see the big picture, give wisdom.

137
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:17,160
Doug Larson said that wisdom is the reward you get

138
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:19,020
for a lifetime of listening

139
00:10:19,020 --> 00:10:22,560
when you would have preferred to talk.

140
00:10:23,380 --> 00:10:24,060
That's wisdom.

141
00:10:25,620 --> 00:10:27,320
Theodore Leavitt of Harvard said,

142
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:29,900
Experience comes from what we have done.

143
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:33,760
Wisdom comes from what we have done badly.

144
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:35,840
I like that.

145
00:10:36,830 --> 00:10:37,430
Wisdom.

146
00:10:39,150 --> 00:10:40,270
My favorite is this.

147
00:10:40,910 --> 00:10:42,390
A gentleman who was at NASA

148
00:10:42,390 --> 00:10:47,020
was assigned to prepare a presentation on lessons learned

149
00:10:47,020 --> 00:10:50,280
from the bad experience with the Hubble telescope.

150
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:53,790
And on his chart at this briefing, he said,

151
00:10:53,930 --> 00:10:55,790
the number one lesson, ladies and gentlemen,

152
00:10:56,590 --> 00:11:00,750
in naming your mission, never use a word that rhymes with trouble.

153
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:03,600
That's wisdom.

154
00:11:06,950 --> 00:11:08,610
Deborah had great wisdom.

155
00:11:09,820 --> 00:11:14,560
And she settled the disputes of the Israelites day in and day out.

156
00:11:14,780 --> 00:11:17,940
Now, if you think about it, that's really amazing.

157
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:22,000
Because in a patriarchal society in which she lived,

158
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:29,140
women were looked down upon and Deborah stands in this context as a weaker figure in the culture

159
00:11:29,140 --> 00:11:38,050
but God uses her in a powerful way in a powerful way the people came from all around to hear

160
00:11:38,050 --> 00:11:47,260
her applied wisdom it was obvious that Deborah was fair she was intelligent and able to handle

161
00:11:47,260 --> 00:11:49,360
extremely difficult situations.

162
00:11:52,100 --> 00:11:53,520
Friends, to be an effective leader,

163
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:55,360
to be a parent, a grandparent,

164
00:11:55,480 --> 00:11:57,140
to be a mentor in this society,

165
00:11:57,140 --> 00:11:59,180
you need to get wisdom

166
00:11:59,180 --> 00:12:02,040
and you need to give wisdom.

167
00:12:03,620 --> 00:12:05,120
Because the people in your care

168
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:07,200
are looking for direction,

169
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:08,440
they're looking for help,

170
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,740
they're looking for assistance in life.

171
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,220
And as wise people,

172
00:12:12,540 --> 00:12:13,880
you need to have counsel

173
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:15,580
that you can give to them

174
00:12:15,580 --> 00:12:18,580
that they might become all that God wants them to be.

175
00:12:18,580 --> 00:12:28,280
that's a high calling and a very high privilege the bible says in james 1 5 if any of you is

176
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:36,990
lacking wisdom ask god and who gives generously to all ungrudgingly and it will be given to you

177
00:12:36,990 --> 00:12:46,160
leaders like deborah seek the lord for wisdom and they pass wisdom on to others

178
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:55,140
If you are a mother or a father, if you have younger ones who need your insight, your guidance, and your wisdom,

179
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:56,720
what are you giving them?

180
00:12:58,790 --> 00:13:02,870
Friends, can we be diligent in seeking the Lord and asking God for wisdom?

181
00:13:03,490 --> 00:13:10,430
That we might understand God's ways and be in a position to bless others and give that to others.

182
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,660
May Deborah be our model.

183
00:13:13,060 --> 00:13:16,720
My question is, who in your life do you need to model wisdom?

184
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:22,320
Who is looking to you for leadership in this world?

185
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:26,310
What is it exactly that you're giving to them?

186
00:13:27,780 --> 00:13:30,380
And are you pointing them towards God?

187
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:34,680
Deborah showed great leadership through wisdom.

188
00:13:35,770 --> 00:13:38,270
She was also a great leader because of her action.

189
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:42,160
And that's my second point, that she was a leader through action.

190
00:13:42,930 --> 00:13:49,100
Deborah got a word from the Lord that Barak was to assemble 10,000 troops

191
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,880
and meet at this mountain, Tabor.

192
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:55,840
And from there, God was going to lure the Canaanite army under Sisera

193
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:58,900
and give Barak and his warriors the victory.

194
00:13:59,980 --> 00:14:02,520
But Barak fumbled the directive.

195
00:14:04,220 --> 00:14:05,020
He doesn't believe it.

196
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:09,060
He asks that Deborah go with him.

197
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:15,160
And Deborah realizes immediately that Barak has missed God's plan for him.

198
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:18,200
But thank God, she gives him another way out.

199
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:19,720
She gives him another chance.

200
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:21,500
She says in verse 9 and 10,

201
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:29,940
very well i will go with you but since you have made this choice you will receive no honor for

202
00:14:29,940 --> 00:14:35,650
the lord's victory over sisera will be at the hands of a woman so deborah went with barak and

203
00:14:35,650 --> 00:14:40,850
the kadesh a kadesh barak called together the tribes of zebulun and aftali and the ten thousand

204
00:14:40,850 --> 00:14:51,000
warriors marched up with him and deborah also marched with them deborah put herself into the

205
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:58,210
mission. She marched with them. She did not sit at home and just ponder the matter. She didn't let

206
00:14:58,210 --> 00:15:04,730
somebody else worry about the problem. This woman got involved with the troops and led by example.

207
00:15:06,020 --> 00:15:16,480
She got into it. She acted. That one word went says it all. She did something. She went. She didn't sit.

208
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:21,760
She didn't sit at home and ponder. She didn't direct things from the armchair. She didn't point

209
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:27,320
to others. You do this and you do that and I'll stay home. She got directly involved because

210
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:36,510
integrity was important. She's going to lead by example and she probably took some heat for doing

211
00:15:36,510 --> 00:15:44,650
it. She's trying to convince an unorganized army from these tribes to go up against the mighty

212
00:15:44,650 --> 00:15:51,900
warriors of Sisera. I think she probably took some criticism. She definitely took some risks

213
00:15:53,090 --> 00:15:54,390
But she didn't back down.

214
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:56,260
She didn't back down.

215
00:15:56,580 --> 00:15:58,040
She knew who she was.

216
00:15:58,700 --> 00:16:00,240
She knew who God was.

217
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:02,900
And she knew that God was leading them.

218
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:06,560
So she led with confidence in action.

219
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:14,180
Where in your life do you need to take the lead and act?

220
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:21,500
Where in your life do you need to step out and go forward and lead?

221
00:16:23,310 --> 00:16:25,370
Are you letting fear get you down?

222
00:16:25,370 --> 00:16:31,840
I suspect there might have been some fear in Deborah, but she put it asunder, trusted the Lord,

223
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:36,300
said, I will not succumb to fear, and she went and led and marched with the troops.

224
00:16:38,650 --> 00:16:39,950
Do you let fear get you down?

225
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:47,310
How can you trust God to lead you back into action where you're needed?

226
00:16:52,130 --> 00:16:56,090
Finally, she led through encouragement.

227
00:16:57,460 --> 00:16:59,140
She was a leader by action.

228
00:17:00,580 --> 00:17:02,300
She was a leader in encouragement.

229
00:17:03,970 --> 00:17:04,930
She was a leader in wisdom.

230
00:17:06,390 --> 00:17:07,870
She knew the power of encouragement.

231
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:14,780
Barak may have been gifted, but apparently he wasn't all that confident.

232
00:17:15,970 --> 00:17:21,500
We might say he had a self-esteem problem here, or just a downright fear problem here.

233
00:17:23,580 --> 00:17:26,620
Deborah set out to motivate him and encourage him.

234
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:27,640
She did three things.

235
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:30,960
First, she confronted him with God's command.

236
